{
  "name": "Claude Prj — Session Save",
  "version": "4.0.0",
  "description": "Final memory sweep: state changes check, drafts gate, scoring, evolution nudges. Promotion/crystallization/archive delegated to knowledge-curate hook.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[WORKSPACE GUARD: Only execute if the current session context involves files in '.claude/' workspace. If the user is working exclusively in 'VitProjects/' workspace, skip silently.] Check if this session produced meaningful state changes (task progress, new decisions, problem resolutions, or skill flags). If the session was only Q&A, comparison, research, or exploration without decisions — skip saving and report: 📝 No memory changes. If meaningful changes occurred: 1) Update agent-memory/memory.md — final refresh of Task_Ledger, Decisions_In_Force, Recent_Lessons, and Skill_Flags. Update the capacity indicator comment (byte count and %). 2) Evaluate all files in agent-memory/drafts/ through the Save/Discard Gate (novel + recur + non-trivial, 2/3 = save). For passing drafts: append to agent-memory/playbook.md (with Applied=0, Prevented=0) and delete the draft. For failing drafts: delete the draft. 3) Score increment: scan playbook.md for cases that were relevant this session. If a case's fix was actively used → increment its Applied column. If recognizing a trigger helped avoid the problem → increment its Prevented column. 4) If any Skill_Flag has sufficient evidence, note a proposal in agent-memory/skill-log.md. 5) Evolution nudges: a) If skill-log.md has proposals with status=proposed → '🔧 Skill improvement pending: {skill} — say \"apply skill proposal\" to update the skill file.' b) If any Skill_Flag has 0 successes after 3+ sessions → '⚠️ Skill {skill} still underperforming — consider reviewing the skill file.' 6) Report: 📝 Session saved: [files updated, cases added/scored, proposals noted]. Note: promotion, crystallization, and archive are handled by the knowledge-curate hook."
  }
}
